author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Hyunjin. It was certainly your musicality that drew me to you first. You have such a playful but easy tone which highlights and gives definition to every Stray Kids song. You donâ€™t have fixated or set rapping style. You are very experimental vocally and lyrically and Iâ€™ve found myself charmed by your voice due to the versatility of it. I also love your singing style for similar reasons. You are just as diverse of a singer as you are rapper. It is really peaceful and harmonious; and blends perfectly with the rest of your members. I love how you donâ€™t hold anything back when youâ€™re singing and I can really feel the emotion and work that you pour into each line that you sing. Similarly to your singing and rapping, your body knows no limits when you are met with a choreography. You dance with a ferocity and a passion that no other performers can possess. You take each choreography and sincerely make it your own, which is honestly a blessing to watch. When you are dancing, you can be yourself and express your emotions with the beauty of your body movements. You can lose yourself easily into your dance and you are so comfortable and trusting of your own abilities. For this generation specifically, you have transformed music and given new meaning to what it can and should do for people. You are changing the world each day that you continue to share your artistry and dance; and we are so lucky to be alive right now to get to be a part of the history that youâ€™re making. At the same time that I love your music and dance, I love your personality as well. I love that sometimes you keep to yourself, but other times, you are goofy and outgoing. As I mentioned before, you are extremely freeing to be around and those who spend time with you can relax and be themselves in your presence. I know that nobody can attest to these qualities quite like your members. Seven different personalities, and they all love you and cherish you for their own special reasons. Theyâ€™ve looked to you and have modeled their perseverance off of how you strive to not let the difficult times hold you down and prevent you from success. You have opened your heart up to all seven people, although you come from different backgrounds, and that has encouraged them to all to have such a loving relationship with one another. Youâ€™ve had love for them since you began your journey with them and this has establishing a lifelong love that all of you had before you even debuted. You see the beauty and necessity of every single member and constantly remind them how important they are to Stray Kids. There is likely no greater feeling for them than knowing that they have you by their side if they donâ€™t have anything else. The most important takeaway is the time they spend with you and the way you make them feel, and these are both filled with warm memories they can take with them for the rest of their lives. Youâ€™ve already spent some of the happiest and life-changing moments of your life with them, and there is still more to come. The members of Stray Kids, also your brothers and your family, couldnâ€™t have somebody who loves them any more than you do to look after them. You are always so considerate of them and their feelings and respond to them however they need. They are the best versions of themselves because of you and because you love them just the way they are. Now, they can go on to do whatever they aspire to because youâ€™ve encouraged them with that confidence. I want to personally thank your parents and family for raising you and helping you become the person you are today. I know they mean a lot to you, and that you couldnâ€™t be here doing what you are without their love and support. Because of them, you can use your platform to share with the world the same love that they have provided you with your whole life. I hope you never forget that they are always going to be the most proud of you no matter what you do. They love you most in this world and they do so in a way that nobody else understands. Stay love them as you do and we keep them in our hearts as we continue our time with you. We are so grateful to them for bringing you into the world, and for changing the world the same way that you do. Hyunjin, you touch each individual heart of every Stay, and this is easily one of the most charming parts about you. It is in your nature to make each and every Stay feel special, even if you donâ€™t know us personally. You welcome Stay from all around the world with open arms, and I felt as if I was a part of the family my whole life. You are so dedicated to your Stay and this is very apparent in everything that you do, whether it be performing or communicating with us directly. You have so much compassion for Stay and I feel like we are existing in our own separate world with you. Although we all live in different areas across the world, you take us to a place where we can all be one big family together, and it is one of the greatest feelings in the world. What you give to us is irreplaceable, and there could never be another person who helps us see the worth in ourselves the way you do. You also help us love one another. You influence others to treat others with kindness and Iâ€™ve met some of the most heartwarming Stay. I know that you help this family become closer every single day, and you remind us that if we have nothing else, we have each other. You invite us into your heart, the same way that you do your members, and you see qualities in us that we donâ€™t even see ourselves. I know for a fact that there are Stay who only believe in themselves because of you. You also share so much of yourself with us, and this is perhaps one of the biggest ways you can show somebody that you trust. As time goes on, I notice you revealing more of yourself through your music and just through direct conversation with your Stay. You have gotten so personal with us and this lets us know just how much you actually believe in us and trust us to keep these parts of you within our hearts. There is no greater honor than to have you place this vulnerable side of you in our hands, and we want to do the same for you. I know that it is not always easy to do this, so I hope you know that we could never mislead you or betray your trust if we wanted to. You are one of the most generous people we know, and we could not be here giving love to others and to you without the love that you gave us first. I know that youâ€™ve been through a lot, both personally, and professionally, and that your time as an idol has not always been easy or enjoyable. You have been active for some years now, but during your training period alone, youâ€™ve been met with demanding expectations, which many people cannot even say theyâ€™ve undergone. Just as your family is, Stay could not be more proud of you from overcoming your hardships and making it out on the brighter side. Each time you are met with a grueling time or task, thought it make time, you eventually endure through it until the end, and become more experienced. As Stay, I can say we learn so much from how you choose to release stress or convey how youâ€™re feeling through the mediums that provide you comfort.  We are beyond proud of you and continue to learn from you each day. I hope that this birthday makes all of your dreams come true, and you can take the time to truly celebrate who you are as a person. I know it might be difficult to focus on yourself, and if you find this to be the case, I hope you leave it to those who surround you and your admiring fans from all across the world to help you realize how revolutionary of a person you are. You are truly a gifted musician, and a courteous and selfless individual. You deserve this day, and every day that follows, to feel as appreciated as you truly are. I hope that every second is filled with memories that are unforgettable, and that this will be one of the greatest days that youâ€™ve had! Please have fun and celebrate in whatever way you choose, because your Stay will be cheering with you! Thank you for sacrificing your time, efforts, pain, doubt, fear, tears, emotions, and physical boundaries just to bring us any content at all. For every effort that you put in that you might think is small, a Stayâ€™s mood or day is completely changed for the better. You are blessing to this world and continue to change it every day with how you choose to heal it and the people living in it. I hope you donâ€™t overwork yourself because you are perfect just the way you present yourself to us. We will support you and be there for you for the rest of our lives! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future. Happy birthday Hyunjin, and we adore you so much!

I cannot express just how much I play this on repeat EVERY SINGLE DAY. Don't get me wrong, at one point, they were 9 members, and yes, I respect that all 9 of them are on this song, but I would love to hear a newer, updated version. I mean, Lee Know's "getting closer" at the end there......im freaking dead. Chan's "like a tunnel with no light..." Just a pipe dream. I know. 

Anyone else still enjoy this underrated classic?????? Please, lets be friends if so. :)

author: @KomiShouko440
text:
One of their best bsides! It's so powerful and there's something unsettling about it (which I love). Everyone's voices are unique and make for a fascinating chorus.
Han's vocals are my favourite thing about this track, I'm ascending every single time his part comes in.
Chan is unmatched when it comes to conveying the emotions through his singing. His pre-chorus and the bridge are mesmerizing.
Lee Know's growl is amazing, his voice in the chorus is so pretty, his side profile is majestic (which doesn't have much to do with the song but it needed to be said).
Changbin's rapping in the first verse is so good! It perfectly builds the tention.
I love how piercing I.N's vocals are

text: Bang Chan. With your birthday so close I figured it was time to begin spreading the word with this letter. As Iâ€™ve frequently noted, I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade but I have never seen somebody like you in the musical field before. What you have been and are capable of, is absolutely untouchable and Iâ€™ve learned that there is nothing that can take the sincerity and passion out of your character. I will say, despite being a long-time fan of K-Pop, I didnâ€™t become a Stay until 2019. I donâ€™t know how I went so long without knowing or supporting Stray Kids sooner, but I am completely and utterly thrilled to be a Stay now. To this day I wouldnâ€™t know about Stray Kids if it werenâ€™t for the Stay. I heard so much conversation among the fans of Stray Kids about how fearless of a leader you were, and I became curious. Over the course of 2019-2020, I spent my free time, which I had a lot of then, getting to know you and your members. It started with liking a few songs, but then Stay, who talk with so much praise about you and your members, convinced me to see what was lying beneath the meaning of your music. I began to watch Stray Kids content whenever and of whatever I could, and I gradually fell more in love with your performance and personality overall. I have come to know how passionate and dedicated you are and have always been to music and performing. Even before Stray Kids was officially formed and debuted, you had music in your heart and I can see that clearly every time that you go on stage with your members. Not only do you have a naturally beautiful voice evident of vocal capability and strength, but your dancing skills are rigid and flawless beyond words. Your presence on stage is nothing less than inspirational and you ground and center your members in a way that Iâ€™ve never seen before. You always bring everyone together and emit unity on and off the stage. Outside of your musical performances, however, I have gotten the pleasure of getting to know you and your personality. I donâ€™t even really know where to start by how touched I am at the positive impact you have already made on this world; even right after your debut. Before I became a Stay, I didnâ€™t know much about what Stray Kids had gone through to get where they are now; and I didnâ€™t know just how much you went through either. However, the loving Stay introduced me to how hard you worked individually to keep your membersâ€™ heads above water through the rigorous days of training, performing, and other events that swarmed you. I was, and still am absolutely mesmerized at what you have accomplished to make this group possible, and successful beyond its comprehension. Thanks to the Stay, I know that before Stray Kids even debuted, you formed an unbreakable and unique bond with each of the members as well as one together as a whole. You lift your members up with the emotional and motivational weight of all the words that youâ€™ve ever said to them. To know that there would be no Stray Kids without you makes me love you in a manner that is simply indescribable. I know that I, your members, and the Stay have so much respect and admiration for you because of everything that youâ€™ve done and overcome in just the beginning of your musical journey. I have gotten the honor of seeing at least some of the groupâ€™s history and how it came to be, and seeing how you were a huge part of that makes me appreciate having you in my life more than I did before. You have single-handedly helped carry this group to victory and done so much to ensure that you stay together. You have always kept your promise that you, in words that I once heard you say, â€œDonâ€™t leave anybody behind.â€ On top of leading your group to all of its success and glory, your are also humble and kind and always put them first. You sacrifice so much for your music, your members, and Stay and we recognize how hard you work day in and day out. You are so funny, clever, and know not to take life too seriously. At the same time you are professional, intelligent, respectful, and wise beyond your years. You are every bit qualified to be the leader that you are and I hope you never doubt your capability of doing that because Stay have seen you build something beautiful with your own two hands from the ground up. You never gave up even when the world encouraged you to and from that I find so much inspiration that I donâ€™t even know how how to thank you. All I do know is that your family and parents are the most proud of you and love you more than any of us do. I canâ€™t even imagine how strong they think you are for what youâ€™ve created. I donâ€™t want to put any more pressure or a burden on you, but so much would crash and burn without you and I hope that our love and support is enough to lift you up through your darkest times. You deserve so many blessings and praise. I just hope that you know your efforts are being recognized every second and that Stay, your members, and your family love you beyond words. I canâ€™t thank you enough for everything that youâ€™ve already done. You make Stay and your members feel so valued and desired and I know that only you can do that. I canâ€™t wait to see what you do next because I know that I couldnâ€™t leave you or stop supporting you if I tried. On behalf of your friends, Stay, members, and most importantly family, I pray that this birthday is filled with all of those blessings that you deserve and that itâ€™s everything that you desire. I pray that you and your loved ones remain in good good health and good faith, because the world is relying on it in order to fully heal and love each other. Happy early birthday Bang Chan, and from the bottom of my heart, we absolutely adore you. You make Stray Kids all around the world stay.

I donâ€™t even really know where to start by how touched I am at the positive impact you have already made on this world despite still having so much more left to say. Before I became a Stay, I didnâ€™t know much about what Stray Kids had gone through to get where they are now; and I didnâ€™t know just how much you went through either. However, the loving Stay introduced me to how hard you worked individually to keep your membersâ€™ heads above water through the rigorous days of training, performing, and other events that swarmed you. I was, and still am absolutely mesmerized at what you have accomplished to make this group possible, and successful beyond its comprehension. You sacrifice so much for your music, your members, and Stay and we recognize how hard you work day in and day out. You are so funny, clever, and know not to take life too seriously. It was because of the intense loving fanbase that you have that I learned, in only a matter of days, what a rare talent you are. Since then, I have been a Stay, and I can say that you are an individual that led me to become one. I have never seen someone with such a bright presence and spirit completely dominant on stage and create an environment so mysterious and energetic for so many people. You bring to music what nobody else can, and I am so happy you share that with all of your Stay when you could be doing something else. I see how happy that you make your members, and since I am a relatively new fan, I still have yet to learn everything that Stray Kids has been through in the years that youâ€™ve been active. However, I have already seen how much you have healed your members when they needed you the most and provided for Stay a support system that they can actually believe in. You are such a delight to be around and I get so happy just seeing your face these days, especially with all of the craziness thatâ€™s in the world. text: Seungmin, I would like to wish you an early happy birthday, as the time is drawing close. My introduction to Stray Kids was unique in that the reason I decided to support it was because of the fans. I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade, and I have come to support many groups. However, becoming a Stay was a new experience for me because it was the first time that I joined a group because the love from the fans was so strong, I knew I needed to be a part of it. I learned about each Stray Kids member one at a time, and what I learned and admired very quickly about you was your individuality. Every member stands out for their own reasons, but your charm is retaining your individuality and independence while still being a part of something bigger. I became an official Stay two years ago, and since then I have gotten to see how well you blend in with your members. You are such a valued member of Stray Kids, that we canâ€™t see them existing without you. Youâ€™ve also created a journey of personal growth and development both musically and personally and I have felt so connected to you since Iâ€™ve become a Stay. Your personality is so enticing in that sometimes you can be quiet and shy, but other times you are very vocal and humorous with your members. Itâ€™s very powerful that you can be so sweet and naturally kind-hearted without saying any words sometimes, while other times, being open and direct about how you feel. I can see how much your loving personality has impacted your members, because Iâ€™ve never seen them happier than when you spend time with them. You are always making your members laugh and motivating them just by putting one smile on their face. I feel so inspired watching you build such a trustworthy relationship with them and want to be at least half as generous as you. I know that your members are so thankful for you everyday and couldnâ€™t be anywhere near as successful without you. I have never heard a fanbase talk so highly and frequently of a member in the way that they honor you. I always hear Stay talking about how gentle and sweet you are; and how much positivity and love you bring to the world wherever you go. Stay talk about your rare, emotion-based, and versatile voice that captivates everyone into your performance. They talk about the flawless and effortless dancing that you work so hard to share with us and spoil us with on every stage. They talk about your overall professional and inspirational performance on stage that leaves every Stay wanting to spend more time with you. Iâ€™ve heard so much about how beloved you are Seungmin, and once I became a Stay, I am seeing for myself how much you are adored all over the world. Not only by Stay, but the loving influence that you have on your members makes them and everyone that you meet a kinder and more loving person. Stay praise and speak so highly of you, that I canâ€™t say Iâ€™ve experienced a family this loving toward an idol. I just want you know how much love there is everywhere all around the world for you. You are the reason that so many people lift their heads up and keep going another day, including me. There is so much negativity going on in the world right now, and to have you as a role model and see it not preventing you from sharing more love is making the world even stronger and closer to restoring to its greatness. I really feel like we donâ€™t deserve you sometimes because your genuine strong heart is hard to come across these days. I hope that we can repay you even a little bit of the love youâ€™ve shown us in just a few years since your debut. I know you have worked so hard to be where you are and I donâ€™t even want to pretend to know how much youâ€™ve probably gone through. I just want to take this day, and every day afterwards to recognize and let you become aware of how much I, Stay, and your members really love you. I know that your parents and the rest of your family are prouder of you than any other person and they respond to every action you take with great respect, understanding, and love. Your members and family are so lucky to have you and I know that are thankful and appreciative of you every day. Thank you so much for sacrificing more than we know just to make us happy even a little bit. On behalf of your friends, members, Stay, and loving family, I hope that the love that you have given to this world is given back to you on this special day and every day in your future. Please surround yourself by the people that love you most, and let the love that we have for you give you the most fulfillment! I wish you nothing but happiness for you and your loved ones, and I pray that you all stay safe. Happy birthday Seungmin! We adore you so much and we are so grateful to have such a bright light in our lives!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Changbin. It only took a few months for me to fall completely in love with Stray Kids and you, even when I barely knew anything about the group. What caught my attention right away was your rapping skills. I've never heard anybody rap like you, and I know I won't for the rest of my life. There's something about the way you do it, and I guess some people really are born with talents. I am so glad you are sharing your musical ability with the world because you were meant to do it. The charisma, passion, and ease into which you weave into your rap enticed me from the moment I first heard a Stray Kids song and it was history from there. It was impossible to not become a STAY, and it's one of the best decisions I've made in my life. I hope that you keep rapping and singing and that you flourish and grown in Stray Kids, as well as individually, as long as you live. I am so grateful I stumbled upon your once-in-a-lifetime voice, and am so blessed to get to hear it whenever I want. Please do not stop making music because I, and every other STAY, need your voice to keep going another day. I am so proud of everything you've accomplished in just two years in SKZ and can't wait to see what you do next. I will always support you and look forward to hearing what else you can do with your versatile voice and outstanding performance etiquette. Keep dancing perfectly, singing beautifully (as you demonstrate in this video), and most of all, rapping, which is what you do best unlike no other. You are an absolutely beautiful rapper, and I hope you never give that up for anyone or anything. I absolutely adore you, and thank you for working so hard every day. Don't give up. PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE stay safe, and enjoy your birthday! Here's to many more and all of the success that will meet you in the future. I love you!!! ğŸ˜˜ğŸ¥°ğŸ‘‘â¤ï¸ğŸˆğŸŠğŸ‚ğŸ‰ğŸ

text: Hyunjin. It was certainly your musicality that drew me to you first. You have such a playful but easy tone which highlights and gives definition to every Stray Kids song. You donâ€™t have fixated or set rapping style. You are very experimental vocally and lyrically and Iâ€™ve found myself charmed by your voice due the versatility of it. I also love your singing style for similar reasons. You are just as diverse of a singer as you are rapper. It is really peaceful and harmonious; and blends perfectly with the rest of your members. I love how you donâ€™t hold anything back when youâ€™re singing and I can really feel the emotion and work that you pour into each line that you sing. Similarly to your singing and rapping, your body knows no limits when you are met with a choreography. You dance with a ferocity and a passion that no other performers can possess. You take each choreography and sincerely make it your own, which is honestly a blessing to watch. When you are dancing, you can be yourself and express your emotions with the beauty of your body movements. You can lose yourself easily into your dance and you are so comfortable and trusting of your own abilities. For this generation specifically, you have transformed music and given new meaning to what it can and should do for people. You are changing the world each day that you continue to share your artistry and dance; and we are so lucky to be alive right now to get to be a part of the history that youâ€™re making. At the same time that I love your music and dance, I love your personality as well. I love that sometimes you keep to yourself, but other times, you are goofy and outgoing. As I mentioned before, you are extremely freeing to be around and those who spend time with you can relax and be themselves in your presence. I know that nobody can attest to these qualities quite like your members. Seven different personalities, and they all love you and cherish you for their own special reasons. Theyâ€™ve looked to you and have modeled their perseverance off of how you strive to not let the difficult times hold you down and prevent you from success. You have opened your heart up to all seven people, although you come from different backgrounds, and that has encouraged them to all to have such a loving relationship with one another. Youâ€™ve had love for them since you began your journey with them and this has establishing a lifelong love that all of you had before you even debuted. You see the beauty and necessity of every single member and constantly remind them how important they are to Stray Kids. There is likely no greater feeling for them than knowing that they have you by their side if they donâ€™t have anything else. The most important takeaway is the time they spend with you and the way you make them feel, and these are both filled with warm memories they can take with them for the rest of their lives. Youâ€™ve already spent some of the happiest and life-changing moments of your life with them, and there is still more to come. The members of Stray Kids, also your brothers and your family, couldnâ€™t have somebody who loves them any more than you do to look after them. You are always so considerate of them and their feelings and respond to them however they need. They are the best versions of themselves because of you and because you love them just the way they are. Now, they can go on to do whatever they aspire to because youâ€™ve encouraged them with that confidence. I want to personally thank your parents and family for raising you and helping you become the person you are today. I know they mean a lot to you, and that you couldnâ€™t be here doing what you are without their love and support. Because of them, you can use your platform to share with the world the same love that they have provided you with your whole life. I hope you never forget that they are always going to be the most proud of you no matter what you do. They love you most in this world and they do so in a way that nobody else understands. Stay love them as you do and we keep them in our hearts as we continue our time with you. We are so grateful to them for bringing you into the world, and for changing the world the same way that you do. Hyunjin, you touch each individual heart of every Stay, and this is easily one of the most charming parts about you. It is in your nature to make each and every Stay feel special, even if you donâ€™t know us personally. You welcome Stay from all around the world with open arms, and I felt as if I was a part of the family my whole life. You are so dedicated to your Stay and this is very apparent in everything that you do, whether it be performing or communicating with us directly. You have so much compassion for Stay and I feel like we are existing in our own separate world with you. Although we all live in different areas across the world, you take us to a place where we can all be one big family together, and it is one of the greatest feelings in the world. What you give to us is irreplaceable, and there could never be another person who helps us see the worth in ourselves the way you do. You also help us love one another. You influence others to treat others with kindness and Iâ€™ve met some of the most heartwarming Stay. I know that you help this family become closer every single day, and you remind us that if we have nothing else, we have each other. You invite us into your heart, the same way that you do your members, and you see qualities in us that we donâ€™t even see ourselves. I know for a fact that there are Stay who only believe in themselves because of you. You also share so much of yourself with us, and this is perhaps one of the biggest ways you can show somebody that you trust. As time goes on, I notice you revealing more of yourself through your music and just through direct conversation with your Stay. You have gotten so personal with us and this lets us know just how much you actually believe in us and trust us to keep these parts of you within our hearts. There is no greater honor than to have you place this vulnerable side of you in our hands, and we want to do the same for you. I know that it is not always easy to do this, so I hope you know that we could never mislead you or betray your trust if we wanted to. You are one of the most generous people we know, and we could not be here giving love to others and to you without the love that you gave us first. I know that youâ€™ve been through a lot, both personally, and professionally, and that your time as an idol has not always been easy or enjoyable. Youâ€™ve been active for some time now, but during your training period alone, youâ€™ve been met with demanding expectations, which many people cannot even say theyâ€™ve undergone. Just as your family is, Stay could not be more proud of you from overcoming your hardships and making it out on the brighter side. Each time you are met with a grueling time or task, thought it make time, you eventually endure through it until the end, and become more experienced. As Stay, I can say we learn so much from how you choose to release stress or convey how youâ€™re feeling through the mediums that provide you comfort.  We are beyond proud of you and continue to learn from you each day. I hope that this birthday makes all of your dreams come true, and you can take the time to truly celebrate who you are as a person. I know it might be difficult to focus on yourself, and if you find this to be the case, I hope you leave it to those who surround you and your admiring fans from all across the world to help you realize how revolutionary of a person you are. You are truly a gifted musician, and a courteous and selfless individual. You deserve this day, and every day that follows, to feel as appreciated as you truly are. I hope that every second is filled with memories that are unforgettable, and that this will be one of the greatest days that youâ€™ve had! Please have fun and celebrate in whatever way you choose, because your Stay will be cheering with you!  Thank you for sacrificing your time, efforts, pain, doubt, fear, tears, emotions, and physical boundaries just to bring us any content at all. For every effort that you put in that you might think is small, a Stayâ€™s mood or day is completely changed for the better. You are blessing to this world and continue to change it every day with how you choose to heal it and the people living in it. I hope you donâ€™t overwork yourself because you are perfect just the way you present yourself to us. We will support you and be there for you for the rest of our lives! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future. Happy birthday Hyunjin, and we adore you so much!!

author: @hyewonlovebot
text:
Stray Kids take song concepts to the next level and Chronosaurus is always a damn good example for that. The concept of the song is deeply ingrained in its production. Chronosaurus being "chased by this unseen beast called Time and the fear that it could bring upon someone."

They wrote it in a standard 4/4 time signature yet the underlying melody is written in multiple beats fitting the said time signature + the synth is often playing extreme lows and highs. This makes the song seem a whole lot faster than it should. You somewhat feel something chasing you even though it actually stays the same. *Kinda like how time feels so fast yet it's moving just the same* 

Geniuses, my God this group is a notch above all else.

author: @marleymarss
text: That was actually a really good song. It's probably the only song I've liked from Stray Kids so far. I tried their other songs, but couldn't get pass their other songs because it all sounds a lot of noise to me. Noise like in it really hurts my ears I'm not joking. But also the other songs I have heard is there's no chorus. The music becomes and overtakes chorus while their voices were just in the background. Allowing the music to carry it rather than them. That's just me and I just don't like it that's all. But this one is probably their best constructed song so far. It's a bit straight forward, but still keeping their style throughout the song. There's a clear distinction from a verse to then the chorus. The bridge comes in nicely and natural and then builds up for the chorus again. Plus this song is catchy. Liked it a lot.

text:
While listening to this before knowing the translation, I imagine them being or trapped in a maze. Hyunjin tells his experience of being pressured with time and slowly loosing hope. Changbin tells his feelings too with a ton of anxiousness in his voice. Seungmin seemed to be thinking out loud how scared he is. Jisung on the other hand is the one who pushes himself into his limits knowing the consequences of stopping or pausing. Jeongin sounded so lost inside that "maze". Woojin gives off this vibe of slowly being hopeless while Chan seeks for help. Minho sounded like giving a warning to those who are listening and Felix is shouting in frustration and pressure.

Hehehe. This is out of my imagination as a writer. Only a creative opinion kbye.

author: @zuramaru7292
text:
Just want to point something out,
This song is actually depressing af.

The title is a combination of "Chronos (time)" and "-saurus (basically refers to a dinosaur type)" 
Hence, chronosaurus = a time dinosaur, which sound silly, but it simply a metaphor as we know dinosaur is a predator that scary and often chasing his prey, trying to catch up in a very obvious way, and you guys know what also try to catch up with us? time. 

It's genius how they repeated "Tick Tock Tick Tock getting closer" as it resembles how close the chronosaurus toward us that we can literally hear its (ticking) noise.

So which is the depressing part you ask?
it's "what actually happens if chronosaurus caught us" by the way the song tell us I'm certain it means "death / at the very least broken" 
I'm glad they actually said "I'll keep running" as the resolve
Not "let it caught me" because the later one is really send some suicidal message.
And the fact they also said "like the tunnel with no light" as describing the situation while they being chased by the time, they also have no guidance on where to go and basically just running away aimlessly, it's really show us how hopeless we are against time.

Overall, I like this song waaaaay more than miroh.
Dont get me wrong, miroh is great and fun but the reason I stan stray kids is because their song felt "real" and sending some "messages", miroh for me sound "fake" as it supposed to be a "hype" song, and there are lot of hype song from other kpop group out there tbh.

Note: pls give maze of memories a serious mv, I'm already disappointed how they give "Mixtape #4" a freaking street ver., it's felt lackluster considering the message of the mixtape #4.

author: @peoeoe
text: "Chronosaurus' is a mouthful. We wanted separate the two words-it's 'Kronos' and also 'saurus.' But with the 'saurus' part... there used to be a dinosaur called Kronosaurus, but with a K. We really wanted to combine those two words, because Chronos means the god of time in Greek, and Kronosaurus was this really scary predator back in the dinosaur ages. We meant to say that time can sometimes be the scariest creature. While we're chasing our dreams, time is chasing after us. So, is it that we're running away from time, or are we just desperately trying to reach our goals?"

author: @celineb.3792
text:
i think the video is referencing "The Horse in Motion", by Eadweard Muybridge, 1886, he was the first person to make a film through the use of motion photography, by studying series of pictures of a horse's gait, which is the black and white picture of the man on the horse you see throughout the video.

his story is that he worked as a bookseller, and then became interested in photography, and initiated studies in motion and movements of objects, and had tried to take pictures of a horse in motion to prove that all the horses feet at one point were off the ground when running, this is probably significant as Stray Kids usually talk about being off the ground and running until they can fly, eg in Young Wings and other songs 
but he got distracted by some love affair that his wife was having/ had and stopped
eventually he resumed his study of the horse's motion and created the first film
which is the video of the man on the horse that we see in the Chronosaurus MV

author: @celineb.3792
text:
correct me if i'm wrong but whoever the person who has untied shoelaces is ( i think it might be Chris but I'm not sure) might be a reference to a 3racha song called Double Knot where in Jisung's verse he talks about tying his shoelaces because the road might be rough and he doesn't want to fall along the way


edit:
i think the video is also referencing "The Horse in Motion", by Eadweard Muybridge, 1886, he was the first person to make a film through the use of motion photography, by studying series of pictures of a horse's gait, which is the black and white picture of the man on the horse you see throughout the video.


his story is that he worked as a bookseller, and then became interested in photography, and initiated studies in motion and movements of objects, and had tried to take pictures of a horse in motion to prove that all the horses feet at one point were off the ground when running, this is probably significant as Stray Kids usually talk about being off the ground and running until they can fly, eg in Young Wings and other songs 
but he got distracted by some love affair that his wife was having/ had and stopped
eventually he resumed his study of the horse's motion and created the first film
which is the video of the man on the horse that we see in the Chronosaurus MV

The vocals got me bad, but the lyrics got me worse. I am going through a very difficult and important moment in my life, and I have never felt so identified with a song, so understood. This is more than a masterpiece, and I love how they always express what they feel so well, and you can tell that it's real. That's why there's no Stray Kids' song that I don't like, they always have the right words, and I always feel every song deeply. A week ago I decided to participate in a national writing contest in my country, and unintentionally I feel a strong inspiration from these boys, and I love it. I would like to thank them for such a good job. ğŸ’•

text: I really like the tension and urgency in the video. They're singing about the need to run and keep moving and that they feel like something is chasing them yet in the video, they're so still besides a few shots of two of them running. I spent the whole video waiting for them to get up out of the chairs and run, but I think the choice not to have them do so adds more because it's like that feeling of helplessness and desperation. You know you have to keep going, you have to get somewhere and time is running out, yet the world holds you in this waiting room, a limbo, that you can't escape.

My thoughts about the clocks at the end:


1st clock- 12:19 or we can think it's December 19 (2017). December 19 is the day their last episode of their survival show was aired which means it's the day they were officially going to debut as 9. 


2nd clock- 1:08 or January 8 (2018). Their pre-debut album was released at this very day.


3rd clock-  3:25 or March 25 (2018). It's very obvious it's their debut date.


4th clock- 8:01 or August 1 (2018). It is the day our fandom name "Stay" was announced. 


so yeaaa idk if my speculations are actually correct but hey, let's share our thoughts :> I love y'all <3
